"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65431","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-08","<p>Changes to the War Pension Scheme would need to be approved by HM Treasury and the Cabinet Office due to the wider impact upon public sector pensions.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-07-08T16:32:21.6000071Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65431/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65431/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65431/answer/previousversion/8610","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-02","War Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will bring forward proposals to amend the rules governing the War Pension Scheme to allow all war widows a pension for life.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","203702"
