"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65433","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>The cost of the HMS Ocean upkeep programme is within the values approved for the project. The final cost will be determined when the contract negotiations for the additional work that was identified during the upkeep period have been concluded between the Ministry of Defence and the Contractor.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-08T16:01:12.3966429Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65433/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65433/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-02","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the contractor is financially liable for the delay in HMS Ocean returning to service from her refit; and what estimate he has made of the costs of that delay.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","203709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65434","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>I am withholding details of the future programme for HMS Illustrious as disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces. However, as first announced on 15 December 2010, (Official Report, column 102WS), HMS Illustrious will retire from service this year.<br><br>The costs associated with the preparation for deployment of any ship are part of the Royal Navy's core activity and are not captured separately.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-07-08T15:48:29.6923499Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65434/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65434/answer","Strategic Defence and Security Review.doc  Hansard Extract  15 December 1210.doc","Strategic Defence and Security Review.doc  Hansard Extract  15 December 1210.doc","Hansard Extract SDSR Royal Navy","Hansard Extract SDSR Royal Navy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65434/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65434/answer/previousversion/8599","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-02","HMS Illustrious","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when HMS Illustrious will be deployed on Exercise Cougar 14; what estimate he has made of the cost of preparing that ship for the exercise; and when she will return to be decommissioned.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","203708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65435","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>All variants of F-35 aircraft, including the UKâs three Joint Strike Fighter F-35B aircraft, are currently under a grounding notice for safety reasons following a fire which occurred on an F-35A on 23 June 2014. A technical investigation is underway to determine the root cause of the incident. F-35 aircraft returned to flying on 16 July 2014. F-35 aircraft will not make a transatlantic flight to the UK this July.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-21T14:18:31.6703519Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65435/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65435/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65435/answer/previousversion/8605","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-02","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the RAF's Joint Strike Fighter 35-Bs have all been grounded following an on-board fire on another Joint Strike Fighter; when the grounded aircraft are expected to fly again; and whether those aircraft will make the transatlantic flight to the UK this July.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","203707"
