"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65449","Department for Education","false","2014-07-08","<p>The Education Funding Agency was created on 1 April 2012. Since then, it has issued four directions to admit to academies. The average time taken to issue these directions was 78 working days. The shortest time was 42 and the longest 142 working days.</p><p>In each case, the EFA encourages academies and local authorities to resolve the matter locally without the need for a formal direction and in most cases this happens. Where a local resolution is not reached, the EFA gathers evidence from the complainant and the academy before issuing its decision.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","203729","2014-07-08T15:44:59.138555Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65449/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65449/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-02","Academies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many requests for directions to admit a child to an academy were received by the Education Funding Agency in 2010; and how many such directions were issued.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","203785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65450","Department for Education","false","2014-07-07","<p>Information on the number of permanent exclusions in each of the last three years is published in the âPermanent and fixed period exclusions from schools in England: 2011 to 2012 academic yearâ Statistical First Release[1]. Information for 2012/13 will be published on 31 July 2014.</p><p> </p><p>Table 1 in the publication shows the number of permanent exclusions in state-funded primary and secondary schools. This information is not available by middle and upper schools, as such schools are deemed either primary or secondary and are included in those counts.</p><p> </p><p>[1]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/permanent-and-fixed-period-exclusions-from-schools-in-england-2011-to-2012-academic-year" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/permanent-and-fixed-period-exclusions-from-schools-in-england-2011-to-2012-academic-year</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-07-07T14:39:31.1115576Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65450/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65450/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-02","Pupil Exclusions: Staffordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children were permanently excluded from (a) primary, (b) middle, (c) upper and (d) secondary schools in Staffordshire in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","203786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65451","Department for Education","false","2014-07-07","<p>The information requested has been placed in the House Library.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-07-07T15:39:46.3453964Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65451/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65451/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-02","Pupils: Speech and Language Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of pupils in (a) reception, (b) year 1 and (c) year 2 in each state-funded primary school had speech and language difficulties in the latest year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","Burton","Andrew Griffiths","203737"
