"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65487","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-07","<p>We have not received any specific reports of Rohingya people being imprisoned for getting married. However, we remain deeply concerned about the situation of the Rohingya, including in relation to discriminatory marriage practices reported in Rakhine State.</p><p>The British Government is one of the most vocal and active members of the international community in supporting those calling for human rights and democracy in Burma. We will continue to urge the Burmese government to take action to protect the lives and rights of Rohingya, and to address the underlying causes of ethnic and religious discrimination and violence.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-07T14:02:33.6224322Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65487/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65487/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received of the imprisonment of ethnic Rohingya people for getting married.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","203632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65488","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-08","<p>Reports from independent international observers of the census suggest that, with the exception of Rakhine State and parts of Kachin State, the enumeration process appears to have largely been carried out effectively. Regarding the process in Rakhine and Kachin, I refer the honourable Member to the answer that I gave to the hon. Member for Belfast East (Naomi Long) on 26 June, Official Report, column 255W. We continue to monitor the process closely.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-07-08T10:38:23.4282Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65488/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65488/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he considers that the recent census in Burma meets international standards.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","203633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65489","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-07","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office offered practical support to the Israeli authorities to help find the kidnapped teenagers.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-07-07T11:53:11.1942823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65489/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65489/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65489/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department took to help secure the release of Eyal Yifrah, Gilad Sha'ar and Naftali Frankel, who were abducted in the West Bank on 12 June 2014.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","203659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65490","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-07","<p>The Government welcomed the decision to review these cases in a civilian court and the drop all charges relating to freedom of expression in 2012, but we understand that other serious charges against the individuals remain. At the time that these individuals were originally convicted, reports acknowledged by the Bahrain Independent Commission of Inquiry suggested that some defendants had been abused in detention, denied access to legal counsel and coerced into confessing. We continue to encourage the Government of Bahrain to meet all its human rights obligations and guarantee its citizens the fundamental liberties to which they are entitled.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson","203713 ; 203714","2014-07-07T14:30:05.252881Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65490/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65490/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","Bahrain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has received about the imprisonment of the Bahrain 13.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","203694"
