"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65494","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-07","<p>Through our High Commission in South Africa who cover our relations with Lesotho, we are closely monitoring the political situation in the country, following the decision on 10 June by Lesotho's Prime Minister to prorogue parliament for 9 months (until 27 February 2015). The UK supports the South African Development Community's (SADC) call for all parties to follow the constitution.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-07T14:18:51.3384897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65494/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65494/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","Lesotho","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the current political situation in Lesotho.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","203738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65495","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-09","<p>The United Kingdom is working to prevent violence against women in South Sudan in a number of ways. First, the UK, with the US and Norway (the Troika), is an active member of the peace talks in Addis Ababa and is supporting regional efforts to address the crisis. Secondly, we are supporting the work of the African Union's Commission of Inquiry that will investigate allegations of violence and abuse to ensure accountability. Third, the UK is one of the leading humanitarian donors contributing, around Â£94 million to date, that will help protect the most vulnerable, especially women and girls. And fourth, and crucially in this regard, South Sudan is a country for engagement for the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's (FCO) Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative. The Government signed the Declaration of Commitment to End Sexual Violence in Conflict, and attended the Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict in London on 10-13 June. We will continue to engage the South Sudan Government on how to take this initiative forward.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-09T08:47:45.2715595Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65495/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65495/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","South Sudan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to prevent violence against women in the conflict-affected states of South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Sir Tony Baldry","Banbury","Sir Tony Baldry","203766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65496","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-08","<p>We continue to pursue a resolution to this issue. I have personally written to both Finance Minister Chinamasa and the responsible Minister for Pensions, Minister Goche. I also raised the issue during a meeting with the Zimbabwean Ambassador in London on 30 June. We are in regular contact with the Director of Pensions, with whom officials last met on 12 June. Our Ambassador regularly raises the issue with interlocutors, including most recently on 4 June with the Finance Minister Chinamasa. She also wrote to the Zimbabwe Civil Service Commission in December 2013; we await a response. We remain in regular contact with the interested parties, including the Overseas Service Pensioners Association (OSPA) and the Federal Pensioners Association in Harare.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-08T13:36:31.9731343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65496/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65496/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-02","Zimbabwe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Answer of 29 October 2013, Official Report, column 411W, on Zimbabwe: pension payments, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that British nationals in Zimbabwe receive their pensions.","false","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","203821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65497","Department of Health","false","2014-07-08","<p>Measures to ensure early diagnosis of cancer, including rarer cancers, are discussed monthly by the Public Awareness and Primary Care Steering Group. The group is chaired by NHS England's National Clinical Director for Cancer and has members representing Public Health England (PHE - Marketing and National Cancer Intelligence Network); NHS England, NHS Improving Quality; Cancer Research UK; Macmillan Cancer Support; Department of Health officials and other stakeholders.</p><p> </p><p>Within the last 12 months, PHE ran campaigns on five rarer cancers: the âblood in peeâ campaign for bladder and kidney cancer; the âpersistent bloatingâ campaign for ovarian cancer and; the âpersistent heartburnâ campaign for oesophago-gastric cancer (oesophageal and stomach). PHE's advertising spend on these campaigns was around Â£3 million.</p><p> </p><p>In 2013-14, NHS England made Â£2.3 million available to Strategic Clinical Networks to support early diagnosis of cancer, including supporting the Be Clear on Cancer campaigns. In addition, the Department funds the National Cancer Intelligence Network around Â£600,000 a year to undertake evaluation of the campaigns. These funds form part of the Â£450 million additional funding over four years for early diagnosis of cancer as set out in <em>Improving Outcomes: A Strategy for Cancer</em> (2011).</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","203855","2014-07-08T15:51:13.9364281Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65497/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65497/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-02","Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions his Department has had with Public Health England and NHS England on measures to ensure early diagnosis of rare cancers in the last (a) six and (b) 12 months.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","203856"
