"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65000","Department of Health","false","2014-07-08","<p>The Department has recently issued guidance to help clinicians comply with the requirements of the Abortion Act, including their obligations with regard to the completing of HSA4 forms.</p><p> </p><p>Incorrectly filled in HSA4 forms are returned to the terminating practitioner by the Department of Health until such information is corrected. Establishing the number of forms returned between 2009 and 2013 still pending completion can only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","203419","2014-07-08T15:16:55.5397721Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65000/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65000/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 18 June 2014, Official Report, column 611W, on abortion, how many of the forms returned to registered medical practitioners are pending completion; and what steps he plans to take to ensure that evidence of breaches of the Abortion Act 1967 is referred to the relevant authorities.","false","Biography information for Simon Reevell","Dewsbury","Simon Reevell","203418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65001","Department of Health","false","2014-07-08","<p>Data is not available in the format requested. Information as is available is shown in the attached. Table 1 shows the number and percentage of patients waiting more than four hours for discharge, admission, or transfer from York Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust accident and emergency (A&amp;E) departments: Table 2 shows the mean and median waiting times for assessment, treatment, and departure at A&amp;E departments at York Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-08T14:15:06.6826597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65001/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65001/answer","PQ203410 - Table.docx","PQ203410 - Table.docx","Tables","Tables","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65001/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","York Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of patients attending the accident and emergency department at York Hospital waited longer than four hours before seeing a doctor in 2009-10 and each year since then; and what the average waiting time was in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","203410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65002","Department of Health","false","2014-07-08","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my Rt. hon. Friend, the Minister for the Cabinet Office (Francis Maude), on 7 July 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, columns 5-6W.</p><p> </p><p>A search of the Department's ministerial correspondence database has identified 17,068 ministerial replies sent to hon. Members in the 2013-14 parliamentary session. Of these, 16,687 were sent by letter and 201 were sent by email.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-08T16:51:39.1662948Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65002/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65002/answer","Simon Kirby Ministerial Replies Cabinet Office.docx","Simon Kirby Ministerial Replies Cabinet Office.docx","Hansard Referral Francis Maude to Simon Kirby","Hansard Referral Francis Maude to Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65002/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will estimate the total number of ministerial replies from his Department to hon. Members in a parliamentary session; and what proportion of such replies are sent (a) by letter and (b) by email.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","203306"
