"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65021","Department of Health","false","2014-07-07","<p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre does not collect any data on the number of adults with autism accessing care and support under the Fair Access to Care Services eligibility criteria.</p><p> </p><p>The Care Act 2014 clarifies and strengthens local authorities' responsibilities towards people who are at risk of abuse or neglect. It places adult safeguarding on a statutory basis for the first time. Information on how many adults with autism in England who receive support because they have been identified by a local authority as being at risk of abuse or neglect is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","203257","2014-07-07T14:15:28.2337999Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65021/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65021/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65021/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","Autism: Cambridge","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many adults with autism accessed care and support under the Fair Access to Care Standards eligibility criteria in Cambridge constituency in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Huppert","Cambridge","Dr Julian Huppert","203256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65022","Department of Health","false","2014-07-07","<p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre does not collect any data on the number of adults with autism accessing care and support under the Fair Access to Care Services eligibility criteria.</p><p> </p><p>The Care Act 2014 clarifies and strengthens local authorities' responsibilities towards people who are at risk of abuse or neglect. It places adult safeguarding on a statutory basis for the first time. Information on how many adults with autism in England who receive support because they have been identified by a local authority as being at risk of abuse or neglect is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","203256","2014-07-07T14:15:28.3018354Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65022/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65022/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65022/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many adults with autism in England receive support because they have been identified by a local authority as being at risk of abuse or neglect.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Huppert","Cambridge","Dr Julian Huppert","203257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65023","Department of Health","false","2014-07-07","<p>The Department's view is that spectacles or contact lenses can satisfactorily correct almost all refractory errors in a safe, cost-effective way.</p><p> </p><p>Clinical commissioning groups have the discretion to pay for a multi-focal lens on the National Health Service if it is judged clinically necessary for an individual patient.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-07T15:46:54.6085625Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65023/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65023/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65023/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","Spectacles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he expects the new Symfony Lens to be available on the NHS as an alternative to glasses.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","203228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65024","Department of Health","false","2014-07-08","<p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre does not collect any data on the number of adults with autism accessing care and support under the Fair Access to Care Services eligibility criteria.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","203400","2014-07-08T14:55:21.3416278Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65024/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65024/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65024/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-01","Autism: Stretford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many adults with autism accessed care and support under the Fair Access to Care Standards eligibility criteria in Stretford and Urmston constituency in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","203244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65025","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>I can confirm that the Department's special advisers are security cleared to <br>the appropriate national security vetting level deemed necessary for the <br>requirements of the post.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-08T14:24:36.4072899Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65025/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65025/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65025/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65025/answer/previousversion/8363","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether all her Department's special advisers have undergone developed vetting.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","203251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65026","Home Office","false","2014-09-01","<p>At the end of December 2011, 1,897 asylum applications from main applicants were pending an initial decision after 12 months, 2,561 at the end of December 2012 and 3,773 at the end of December 2013. <br><br>The figures provided are a subset of latest published statistics for applications received for asylum since April 2006 which are published by the Home Office on a monthly and quarterly basis. <br><br>The latest release Immigration Statistics January to March 2014 is available from:<br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-january-to-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-january-to-march-2014</a> <br>and from the Library of the House. Asylum data tables (volume 1) are available from: <br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/311790" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/311790</a><br>/asylum1-q1-2014-tabs.ods<br><br>Our aim this year is to ensure all claims made before April 2014 have an asylum decision by 31 March 2015. Furthermore, we are endeavouring to ensure all new claims received since 1st April 2014 get a decision within the 6 months service standard.<br><br>We are raising our decision-maker productivity targets in order to deal with rising intake, and we are continually recruiting new caseworkers to maintain appropriate staffing levels and to support our aim to get within service standards by the end of the 2014/2015 period.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-09-01T13:56:49.1866078Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65026/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65026/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65026/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum seekers had been waiting for an initial decision on their asylum application for more than one year at the end of (a) 2011, (b) 2012 and (c) 2013.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","203287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65027","Home Office","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>The Home Office does not hold this information.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-07-07T13:25:26.3246267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65027/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65027/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65027/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Nazi War Crimes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many investigations have been carried out by Scotland Yard since 1984 on suspected individuals involved in crimes by the SS in the Second World War.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","203227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65028","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>I refer the Hon. Member to the reply given on 30 June 2014, Official Report, <br>column 377W.<br>National Crime Agency intelligence packages are disseminated to the most <br>appropriate police force based on information drawn from an investigation. This <br>was the case in Operation RESCUE/CALANDO.<br>The information requested on the number of intelligence packages sent to each <br>police force in the UK is operational and cannot be released because of the <br>possibility that there are related investigations or judicial processes <br>ongoing.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-07-08T14:16:50.7362674Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65028/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65028/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65028/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Offences against Children: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2014, Official Report, column 666W, on offences against children: internet, whether the intelligence packets were divided up into police authority areas based on the address of the suspected purchaser; and how many intelligence packages were sent to each police force in the UK.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","203249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65029","Home Office","false","2014-07-09","<p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice Court Proceedings Database holds information on <br>defendants proceeded against, found guilty and sentenced for criminal offences <br>in England and Wales. However, it is not possible from this centrally held data <br>to identify those charged with and convicted of being members of individual <br>organisations. This detailed information is not reported to Justice Statistics <br>Analytical Services due to their size and complexity.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-09T15:17:21.4923115Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65029/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65029/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65029/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Nazi War Crimes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people since 1984 have been (a) charged with and (b) convicted of being a member of the SS in the Second World War.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","203226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65030","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>The Home Office data on Section 95 claimants is aligned to the specific payment <br>categories. The categories referred to in the question were changed in October <br>2009.<br><br>The Home Office data on Section 95 claimants is aligned to the specific payment <br>categories. The categories referred to in the question were changed in October <br>2009<br><br>[INSERT TABLE HERE]</p><p>NB 5,638 is the number of persons categorised as couples not the number of <br>couples (2,819)</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-08T13:52:12.827",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65030/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65030/answer","Table for PQ203354.xls","Table for PQ203354.xls","PQ203354 Table","PQ203354 Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65030/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65030/answer/previousversion/8354","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Asylum: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum seekers in receipt of Section 95 support are (a) singe adults aged between 18 and 24, (b) single adults aged over 25, (c) couples, (d) single lone parents, (e) aged 16 or 17, (f) children under 16 and (g) children under five.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","203354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65031","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>We do not hold data on the amount of time people stay on section 95 support in <br>a format that is compatible with National Statistics protocols.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-08T14:02:07.3679677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65031/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65031/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65031/answer/previousversion/8351","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Asylum: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how long on average an asylum seeker stays on Section 95 support.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","203355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65032","Home Office","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>The total number of Ministerial replies sent to hon. Members between 1 January <br>and 31 December 2013 was 56,193. This figure includes replies sent by letter <br>or email. We do not collect information centrally on the volumes of responses <br>provided by email and it could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-07T14:26:52.4230456Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65032/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65032/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65032/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will estimate the total number of ministerial replies from her Department to hon. Members in a parliamentary session; and what proportion of such replies are sent (a) by letter and (b) by email.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","203307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65033","Home Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>There are two grades of Asylum caseworkers in UKVI, EO decision makers and HEO <br>senior decision makers. <br>The pay scales for these caseworkers are:<br><br>EO National - Â£22,770 - Â£26,209<br>EO London - Â£26,242 - Â£30,181<br>HEO National - Â£27150 - 32460<br>HEO London - Â£30,388 - Â£36,922<br>We are unable to provide average salary data for UKVI caseworkers. <br>This year we expect to employ an average of 409 caseworkers. Caseworkers are <br>expected to conduct interviews, deal with decisions and take detained fast <br>track appeals. They are expected to work on 225 of these in various <br>combinations in a year.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-14T13:21:58.7918403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65033/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65033/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65033/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65033/answer/previousversion/8349","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","UK Visas and Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average annual salary of a UK Visas and Immigration asylum caseworker is; and how many asylum decisions such a caseworker makes on average in one year.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","203401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65034","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>Information relating to officials' time is not available because the time spent <br>on individual cases is not broken down or recorded. Legal costs to date are <br>Â£109,076.74.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-08T14:25:22.3710757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65034/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65034/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65034/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the total cost to the public purse of (a) officials' time and (b) legal fees was of defending Refugee Action vs the Home Department, case number CO/8523/2013.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","203417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65035","Home Office","false","2014-07-14","<p> </p><p>These questions could only be answered through a disproportionately expensive <br>manual case search to collate the data.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-14T12:43:57.9819024Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65035/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65035/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65035/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-01","Asylum: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum seekers were granted permission to work in (a) 2011, (b) 2012 and (c) 2013.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","203389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65036","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p>UK aid to Nigeria is delivered through civil society organisations, technical assistance and UN agencies. DFID does not finance the Government of Nigeria directly. As most UKAID programmes are national in scope, it is not possible to provide regional breakdowns, however since 2011 at least 60% of our funds are focussed on Northern Nigeria. The figures for UK Aid to Nigeria for the last 5 years are:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>Â£117.4m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>Â£131.1m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>Â£171.6m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>Â£196.5m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>Â£ 265.9m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>In 2011, DFID launched a Â£39m Nigeria Stability and Reconciliation Programme, which supports Federal and State Governments and civil society organisations to tackle the causes of violent conflict and to improve coordination within and between state agencies and local populations. The programme operates a grants fund for civil society organisations in priority states in the North, Middle Belt and the Delta.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-08T16:10:52.378181Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65036/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65036/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65036/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Nigeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much UK aid has been provided to Nigeria to stem the escalation of Islamic extremist terrorism in the last five years, (a) in the North and Middle Belt and (b) elsewhere in that country; to whom such aid was provided; and in what form in each such case.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","203395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65037","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p>The information requested is published on our website at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/254053/Table6.csv/preview" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/254053/Table6.csv/preview</a></p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-08T16:08:13.8593567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65037/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65037/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65037/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much official development assistance was spent in 2009-10 and each year since then (a) in cash terms, (b) at current prices and (c) as a proportion of UK gross national income (i) in total, (ii) by her Department, (iii) by the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, (iv) by the Ministry of Defence, (v) by the Department for Energy and Climate Change and (vi) by other Government departments.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","203359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65038","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p>Both boys and girls are being helped by the Myanmar Education Consortium (MEC). The MEC is working across Burma and expects to reach all the major ethnic groups of Burma and the three major religions: Buddhist, Christian, and Muslim.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-08T16:09:56.3940022Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65038/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65038/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65038/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the (a) gender, (b) ethnicity and (c) religion are of the 160,000 children proposed to be helped by the Myanmar Education Consortium.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","203375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65039","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>DFID does not have any programmes which work on private health insurance in Burma. DFID's key support is through the Three Millennium Development Goal fund, which works to strengthen public healthcare systems as well as to contract some private services where they can fill gaps in public provision.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-08T16:08:51.5545466Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65039/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65039/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what role private health insurance plays in her Department's plans to promote healthcare in Burma.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","203373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65040","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>Of the Â£10 million committed to the census, Â£9 million has already been disbursed. The remaining Â£1m is for data analysis, thematic reports and the dissemination of information.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-08T16:09:33.653905Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65040/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65040/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether it is her policy to continue funding the official census in Burma.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","203374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65041","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>The Department for International Development annually publishes details of its bilateral spend to countries in its Statistics on International Development (SID). The most recent publication can be found by following the link below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/statistics-on-international-development-2013-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/statistics-on-international-development-2013-tables</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Bilateral aid, or Official Development Assistance (ODA), is a cash transaction. Current price figures are the same as the cash figure in the year they were reported.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-08T16:07:32.2883691Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65041/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65041/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Bilateral Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much was spent in bilateral aid in each country with a UK bilateral aid programme (a) in cash and (b) at current prices in 2009-10 and each year since.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","203358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65042","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>I refer Hon. Member to the answer provided yesterday by my Rt Hon. Friend the member for Horsham (Mr Maude), <em>Official Report</em>, Column 5W .</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan","203531","2014-07-08T16:02:20.8635429Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65042/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65042/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will estimate the total number of ministerial replies from her Department to hon. Members in a parliamentary session; and what proportion of such replies are sent (a) by letter and (b) by email.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","203308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65043","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>DFID has contributed to a food security programme in Chin State through the Livelihoods and Food Security Trust Fund which is helping increase agricultural production through activities such as better quality seeds, and also helping farmers get their produce to markets.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-07-08T16:07:01.1151685Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65043/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65043/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment her Department has made of reports of a food crisis in Chin State, Burma; and what food support her Department is providing in that region.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","203271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65044","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>To provide an itemised list of goods and services from private sector suppliers for each financial year from 2009 forward detailing spends between developed and developing countries would incur disproportionate costs to my department.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-08T16:05:21.5256638Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65044/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65044/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much Official Development Assistance (ODA) was spent (a) in cash terms, (b) at current prices, as proportion of total UK ODA in 2009-10 and each year since then on procuring (i) goods and (ii) services from private sector suppliers with their head office based in (A) developed and (B) developing countries.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","203237"
