"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65046","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>To provide an itemised list of goods and services as a proportion of total bilateral aid spend in each country for each financial year from 2009 forward detailing spends would incur disproportionate costs to my department.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-08T16:06:36.0559926Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65046/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65046/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Bilateral Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much bilateral aid in each country with a UK bilateral aid programme was spent (a) in cash terms, (b) at current prices, (c) as a proportion of that country's total bilateral aid programme in 2009-10 and each year since on procuring (i) goods and (ii) services from private sector suppliers based in the country concerned.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","203239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65047","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>The information requested is published in our Annual Reports, the most recent of which is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/annual-reports-and-accounts-2012-13" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/annual-reports-and-accounts-2012-13</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We do not disaggregate humanitarian assistance in the form requested, but disaggregation by country over the time period is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210430/Total-UK-Net-ODA-Humanitarian-Assistance-recipient-country1.csv/preview" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210430/Total-UK-Net-ODA-Humanitarian-Assistance-recipient-country1.csv/preview</a></p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-07-08T16:04:36.6732807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65047/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65047/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-01","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much (a) in cash terms, (b) at current prices, (c) as a proportion of UK Official Development Assistance (ODA) and (d) as a proportion of UK Gross National Income was spent by the UK on ODA in 2009-10 and each year since (i) in total, (ii) on multilateral aid, (iii) on bilateral aid (A) in total, (B) in high and middle income countries, (C) in low income countries and (D) in least developed countries (1) on humanitarian relief and (2) for other purposes.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","203235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65048","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-08","<p>The requested information is not held centrally and would need to be collated through enquiries at each prison in England and Wales. This would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-07-08T14:33:53.1721113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65048/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65048/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Prison Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many training and education sessions in each prison in England and Wales were cancelled due to staff shortages in each month in 2013.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","203242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65049","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-08","<p>It has not been possible to answer this Question within the time available. I will write to the Hon Lady as soon as possible.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-07-08T16:40:11.4387332Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65049/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65049/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much HM Prison Service spent on severance pay for staff at prison officer grades in each year from 2010 to 2013.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","203243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65050","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-08","<p>There are 302 magistrates serving in Teesside. Of this total number, 151 are male and 151 are female. The ethnic composition of the bench in Teesside is as follows:</p><p>White - <strong>288</strong></p><p>Mixed - <strong>2</strong></p><p>Black - <strong>0</strong></p><p>Asian â<strong>10</strong></p><p>Chinese â <strong>0</strong></p><p>Any other - <strong>2</strong></p><p>A total of 25 new magistrates were recruited to the bench in Teesside in the last three years; 18 of these new appointments were made in 2012-2013 and seven of the new appointments were made in 2013-2014. No new recruitment took place for the Teesside bench in 2011-2012.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-07-08T15:34:02.9155904Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65050/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65050/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Magistrates: Tees Valley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many magistrates there are on Teesside; what the gender and ethnic composition of that bench is; and what recruitment there has been to that bench in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","203266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65051","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-08","<p>HM Prison Service Reserve has been established as a permanent pool of experienced prison staff which can be deployed to areas of the country where and when there is a temporary need There is no limit on the number of former officers who may join The Reserve.<em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p>1375 ex-prison officers invited to express interest left under one of a number of voluntary early departure schemes supporting the closure of prisons or other efficiency programmes.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","203263","2014-07-08T16:55:52.8541075Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65051/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65051/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many ex-prison officers invited to express interest in joining HM Prison Service Reserve received a redundancy package from HM Prison Service between 2010 and 2013.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","203240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65052","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-08","<p>No prison officers working in public sector prisons in England and Wales were made redundant, or took voluntary redundancy between 2010 and 2013.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-07-08T16:53:45.0897989Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65052/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65052/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers working in the prison estate in England and Wales have been made redundant or taken voluntary redundancy in each year from 2010 to 2013.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","203241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65053","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-08","<p>HM Prison Service Reserve has been established as a permanent pool of experienced prison staff which can be deployed to areas of the country where and when there is a temporary need There is no limit on the number of former officers who may join The Reserve.<em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p>1375 ex-prison officers invited to express interest left under one of a number of voluntary early departure schemes supporting the closure of prisons or other efficiency programmes.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","203240","2014-07-08T16:55:52.7224232Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65053/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65053/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many former prison officers his Department plans to hire to join to HM Prison Service Reserve.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","203263"
