"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65069","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-08","<p>As the Hon. Lady will be aware, I set out in my Written Ministerial Statement of 26 June the processes necessary to prepare Lady Justice Hallett's report for publication. In my statement, I confirmed that the report is being prepared for publication by Lady Justice Hallett and that she had informed me that it will be presented to me for the first time on 16 July. I intend to publish Lady Justice Hallett's report 24 hours later.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-08T16:14:12.4792907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65069/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65069/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-01","Administrative Scheme for the "On the Runs" Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, for what reason the publication of the Hallett Report into the On-The-Runs Scheme has been delayed until 17 July 2014; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","203208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65070","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-08","<p>As with the publication of previous reports, I intend to grant advance sight to those whom Lady Justice Hallett has recommended as being interested parties. This will include representatives of the families of the victims of the Hyde Park bombing in 1982.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-08T16:11:29.6360185Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65070/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65070/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-01","Administrative Scheme for the "On the Runs" Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps she is taking to ensure that the families of the soldiers killed in the Hyde Park Bombing of 20 July 1982 will have early sight of the Report of Lady Justice Hallett into the On-The-Runs Scheme due to be published on 17 July 2014; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","203209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65071","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-07","<p>The majority of the information in the file has been disclosed. An application for closed information in the file is currently subject to a pending appeal in the First-tier tribunal. Therefore the Government cannot comment further in these circumstances.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-07-07T16:46:00.2261554Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65071/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/65071/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-01","Jimmy Savile","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will revise his decision to redact documents relating to Jimmy Savile in the PREM 19/878 file in the National Archives.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","203322"
